description:
The latest episode of the TV drama @actor_0@ was cast in had a season finale plot twist that has left critics and fans scratching their heads, and not in a good way.

@actor_0@ was a key character involved in the twist, so a lot of fans' reactions are directed at her.

What should we do about this?

@actor_0@ shared a post from a blogger that was praising [groupname]. However, the person who made the original post is notorious for having controversial views on whaling, and some are attacking @actor_0@ for giving them publicity.

@actor_0@ was not aware of this, but a lot of fans noticed and are pointing it out.

What should you do?

@actor_0@ recently liked and linked to an art post on her social media account. While the art in question seems to be inoffensive, it turns out that the artist who created it is notorious for being arrested several years ago for possession of "illicit material."

Now people are mad because @actor_0@'s like is seen as an "endorsement" of this artist.

@actor_0@ deleted her link to the post, but not before people took screenshots of it to circulate online.

What should be done?

result.description:
@actor_0@ did lose her temper on stream, but she didn't throw the first punch: if trolls don't want to be 'belittled,' they should play nice to start with.

That's the sentiment expressed in the announcement that gets sent out from the official [groupname] account, defending @actor_0@ for her actions. The reaction is split: some continue to criticize @actor_0@ for her outburst, but others are sympathetic, noting that she should have the right to defend herself in the face of trolls.

The public statement has the effect of redirecting most of the vitriol away from @actor_0@ and toward the official group account for defending her. @actor_0@ seems appreciative to no longer be the one at the center of the controversy.

description:
Your sound technician, @actor_1@, has come to you recently to complain about a bizarre undertone in the bass of your recent recordings that he's compared to 'a human heartbeat, but like, dying'. 

@actor_0@, who was the last one practicing in the room, has heard it on her tracks and is absolutely CONVINCED the room is haunted. She refuses to continue practicing in the studio until the matter is resolved. Some of the other girls are supporting her in a strike of sorts. 

You’ve listened to the recordings yourself, but you aren't able to hear anything off. Bizarre. Still, you probably won't hear the end of this until you make a decision. What will you do?

result.description:
If it's going to affect the quality of the recording, perhaps it's best to hire an expert to deal with the issue. It would be a shame if recordings were ruined due to a technical glitch.

After conducting a thorough investigation, the expert concludes that everything seems to be in working order, but giving the interiors a good dusting could prove beneficial. Sure enough, the next time the studio is used, everything seems to be back to normal.

@actor_0@ seems annoyed by the decision to take a technical approach to resolving what she believes is a supernatural event, but she can't deny that whatever problem existed before seems to have been dealt with.

description:
Oh no! @actor_0@ just got a little too competitive in the latest episode of [groupname]'s regular game show [show_game] and was caught blatantly cheating to win! Everyone on the show laughed it off as silly antics, but not everyone is so amused.

Now, @actor_0@ is pegged as a filthy cheating criminal, with wild rumors spreading about how she's a habitual cheater, with stories ranging from cutting in line at train stations to forged high school entrance exam results.

@actor_0@ is worried that these wild rumors will start to affect her professional reputation. What should we do?

result.description:
@actor_0@ didn't like the image change, but she gained some audience from the trouble-making pranksters all over the country.

The public likes a story, and the story that @actor_0@ is a habitual mischief-maker seems to successfully replace the story that she's a habitual cheater. Nobody likes a selfish fraud, but anyone can tolerate a little playful mischief.

@actor_0@ still isn't too happy with having the image of an "impish" personality, but admits it's better than being seen as a cheater.

@actor_0@ records a video sharing how touched she was by the fan's story...and admitting that she felt a bit awkward, because she actually wasn't involved.

She ends with an upbeat message: "I think this story shows that anyone can be a good host when greeting visitors to a new city. You don't have to be famous to be helpful!"

@actor_0@'s positivity seems to draw even more praise from people who salute her for telling the truth and encouraging fans to be helpful to strangers.

description:
A viral video has been circulating. Apparently @actor_0@ lost her temper when a malfunctioning vending machine ate her money and didn't give her a drink, and she decided to take out her rage and frustration on the machine by kicking it.

@actor_0@ won't be facing any property damage fines, since the only thing she damaged by kicking the vending machine was her own foot, if the howls of pain heard in the video are anything to go by. Worst of all, someone was there to record the entire incident and share it online.

Some responses to the video laughingly mock @actor_0@ for her self-inflicted pain, while others are berating her for losing her temper in public. This is starting to get out of hand.
